From b64a09c3056808af4c3c2c93a8ae511ad623d523 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: genspark_dev <genspark_dev@genspark.ai>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 21:07:22 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix RF 'reads once then stops': revert to open-per-read
 pattern

The native RFCardInterface.searchEnd() safety-net (patch 8) left the
reader in a broken state so no card was detected at all. Root cause:
keeping one long-lived RF handle + native search session open across
polls repeatedly wedged the reader.

Revert NFC to the simple, proven OPEN-PER-READ pattern:
- openRfDevice(): resolve device name reflectively, open a FRESH handle
  each cycle, skipRATS. No caching, no low-power detect latch.
- readNfcOnce(): open -> waitForCardPresent -> getCard/getID/type, and
  ALWAYS close the handle in a finally block.
- Removed ensureRfDevice()/releaseRfDevice()/releaseSearchSession() and
  the native searchEnd() call entirely.
- Still runs on the io background thread (no ANR).
- nfcDiag now does a quick open/close probe.

Keeps SUCCESS==1 check, reflective device-name resolution, diagnostics.
